    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "3.1 LLM-based Vulnerable Code Block Identification The first step progressively narrows down the location of vulnerable code through two stages. It begins with coarse-grained method localization, identifying methods likely associated with the vulnerability based on contextual signals such as CVE descriptions, commit messages, and surrounding code. Building on this, the module then performs fine-grained analysis to isolate the specific code blocks within those methods that directly correspond to the vulnerable behavior. By combining these two stages, the module achieves both breadth and precision in identifying the code regions most relevant to the vulnerability.",
